channel.title: Privacy Act Issuances - New items on govinfo
channel.description: Provides access to newly published GovInfo content from the Privacy Act Issuances. The Office of the Federal Register (OFR) biennially compiles and publishes The Privacy Act Compilation, which includes Federal Agency systems for maintaining records about individuals as well as procedures for individuals requesting information about their records.

image.title: Privacy Act Issuances - New items on govinfo

channel.copyright: Title 17, Section 105, United States Code, provides that: Copyright protection under this title is not available for any work of the United States Government, but the United States Government is not precluded from receiving and holding copyrights transferred to it by assignment, bequest, or otherwise. For more information, see https://www.govinfo.gov/about/policies#copyright
